I am looking for an Analytics lead/ Head of analytics who is able to roll up their sleeves and get their hands dirty. Salary range (net) 300K-400K rub / month and equity (~0.08%-0.12% ). Message me or email me: <mailto:anton@wheely.com|anton@wheely.com>.

Wheely (<https://wheely.com/en/careers>) is a luxury ride-hailing service that operates in London and Moscow (~100 employees, ~2’500 drivers). We are growing fast (>100% YoY) and raising a Series B round to fuel further growth in London and launch Paris next year.
Our key goals are to get our data infrastructure and core analytics team in place (before starting to hire data science talent) in order to solve the following business challenges:
• Data loaded directly from production systems is messy, we want to implement a solid process for data modeling, so that our data models serve as the underlying business logic for all our analytics use cases, from BI to data science.
• Define metrics, especially when there is no consensus among business users. For instance, what do we consider as a journey? Do we use UTC or local time to consolidate them? Do we need a custom close of day?
•Geo is hard. We do have lat/long for every journey pickup for instance, but we are struggling to transform it to something meaningful (eg districts).
• Scale up knowledge (how was metric X produced?) rather than simply data.

We understand that you might not have the expertise required to put together all of the components our tech stack or the experience to solve all of the different analytics problems you’ll face across your business, and we are open to hiring consultants if necessary. The position is based in Moscow or in London (we do not offer visa sponsorship for this role).

*Requirements:*
•A relevant degree (Statistics, STEM, Computer Science, MBA etc)
• Experience in setting up a modern analytics stack (e.g. Sitch, Alooma, Redshift, etc)
• Expert in SQL
• Amazing problem solving abilities.
